8: I... got it! I think I did it!
15: I wish I could be of more help...
19:
There must be something else I can
do!
23:
Um... Lady Phiria, how is it that you
want to help, exactly?
27:
Well, everyone is preparing to fight
the Overlords...
30:
Surely there must be some way I
can help! Something I can do to
protect the people here!
35:
I mean, you've already helped us
repair the abyss with the Voluntas
Splice. I'd say you're doing more
than enough already.
38:
...But something tells me you want to
help out in other ways, too.
42:
Oh, yes. Ever so much. But I'm afraid
I'm not sure how... Ah! If you need
something demolished, my magic
would be more than—
48:
There you are, Phiria! We have
something for you.
53:
It's a letter from Nihilyana. An official
invitation to join Voluntas Academy.
57:
Once she saw your powers, she was
hooked! She says she'd love to have
you at the academy—
62:
Not only as a student, but as a
teacher, too.
72:
Maybe she wants Phiria to give
some special lectures for the
Shibuyan students or something?
76:
I'm not exactly sure. Something
about her having an "aptitude for
stirring things up."
81:
In that case, Lady Phiria is just the
one for the job. Her powers are
peerless.
86:
Er... Phiria doesn't look quite so
confident.
92:
Oh, dear... M-me? A teacher? I
couldn't p-possibly...
96:
I don't have the charisma to give a
compelling lecture... I simply wasn't
blessed with the gift of gab!
105:
There was an article in the Oculus
Times about the qualities that great
teachers possess. Eloquence was
one of them.
109:
However will I manage? I don't have
the way with words a teacher
needs... What if the students don't
even show up to my lectures?
113:
If you're already worried about
student attendance... does that
mean you accept the offer?
117:
Oh, silly me—I accept! I believe I
could make a difference as a
teacher.
122:
Lady Phiria has a habit of getting
ahead of herself... I merely wish for
her to succeed in whatever
endeavor she chooses.
125:
Heh! Then it sounds like you need
me, darlings! Perhaps I can lend a
hand?
129:
If it's charisma you want, first you'll
need to look the part. You just need
to fake it until you make it, right?
133:
We had a design made up for your
new look. Do you like it?
137:
Oh, my... It looks amazing! But... are
you sure this style suits me?
141:
Ah, forgive me... I must be more
confident! I'll do my utmost to
become a teacher worthy of such
fine garments!
145: Heh. You'll be grand, I'm sure of it!
149:
Careful, now... You need to wear the
clothes—not let the clothes wear
you!
154:
That's where I come in, Phiria. With
my help, you'll even be able to go
toe-to-toe with a certain Selphis!
159:
Oh, thank you so much! But would
you mind if I made a suggestion? I
saw this amazing-looking staff in a
manga the other day...
163:
I've never taken a magic course
before... What if they taught us how
to do, like, a magical girl
transformation or something?
That'd be cool!
165:
I heard the new teacher is a sprite
user! And get this, she was invited
here by the headmistress herself!
169:
Cheeks caress and flowers bloom, I
invoke thee, zephyr sweet.
173: O light of hope, guide my hand!
176:
No way! She can summon sprites
AND harness light magic... with
incantations alone?!
181:
My name is Phiria Hermel,
summoner of wind sprites and
commander of the light.
184:
From this point forward, I will teach
you all I know of those worlds. To
hear the voices of the winds... to
walk in the ways of the light.
190:
Wh-whoa, her outfit rebrand sure
did the trick! But can she really back
up all of that talk?
194:
To begin, allow me to demonstrate
my powers.
201:
B-behold! I shall now cut some
vegetables!
209:
Next, I will cook them before your
very eyes!
215:
O light of hope, shine bright! Super
Vegetable Flare!
222:
Mmm, this is great, but... What does
it have to do with magic, exactly?
225: It has EVERYTHING to do with magic!
229:
Don't you see? The fine, even cut of
each piece... The balance and
crunch... Bite-sized and cooked to
perfection!
232:
Magic isn't just for the battlefield. A
true master like Phiria can control
her magic to accomplish the most
delicate of tasks—cooking!
236:
I have learned that with time,
practice, and help from your friends,
anything is possible!
240:
As your teacher, I'll do my very best
to support you every step of the way!
243: S-so... That's all for today! Thank you!
246:
Wait, that's it?! All you did was cut
up some vegetables!
250:
Ah, I... I'm afraid I hadn't planned any
further than this... I p-promise to do
better next time! Now, if you'll excuse
me!
253:
Ms. Phiria, come back! How are you
able to use both wind and light? And
how are we supposed to channel
that kind of magic, anyway?!
255:
Show us again, pleeease! Cut the
veggies up into cute little kitty
shapes this time!
259:
K-kitty... shapes? I'm terribly sorry, I
don't think I can...
263:
Is she really gonna be all right? If
this goes south, I blame Yumu. He's
acting like a total weirdo.
267:
Actually, I think things are going
quite well. Don't give up, my lady...
